To calculate the LIX (läsbarhetsindex, or readability index) score for the given Swedish text, I'll use a formula developed by Karl G. Anderson. This formula involves counting the total number of words, the number of long words (7 or more characters), and the number of complex sentences (more than one clause). The LIX score ranges from around 20 to 100, with lower scores being easier to read.

Here's the given text: 
